"disclosures_text" : "RxSaver is a discount plan only. It is not insurance coverage and may not be used with commercial health plans or any federal or state funded health care program, such as Medicare or Medicaid.

The range of discounts for medications provided by the pharmacies participating in RxSaver vary depending upon the pharmacy and medication provided. Prescription drug pricing fluctuates frequently, therefore pricing is subject to change without notice. Certain states have imposed restrictions on the use of prescription drug coupons and therefore the RxSaver coupons are void where prohibited.

Nothing contained in this app, or any other RxSaver materials, constitutes medical advice. Please consult a medical professional for information about a specific prescription drug product.

You are required to pay for your prescription at the time of service but you may receive a discount from participating pharmacies when you present an RxSaver coupon or discount card. Participating pharmacies are those displayed on the website or mobile app.

If you desire a list of participating pharmacies or need any assistance or information, please contact us toll free at: (855) 569-6337 or from our website at www.rxsaver.com"

"text_how_to" : "RxSaver can help you find a discount on your prescription medications, even if you have health insurance.

Start by searching for your medication. If this is your first time using the app, you will be asked to enter a ZIP code or enable GPS services. Because prescription prices can vary by pharmacy, your location information is needed to find prices at pharmacies near you.

After you have selected a medication, the app will show prices for that drug’s most common form, dosage, and quantity. Change the form, dosage, and/or quantity to match your prescription to find out how much you can expect to pay.

Next, select a pharmacy and click the pink coupon button to get a coupon to show the pharmacist. The pharmacist will use the codes from the coupon to get you a lower price on your prescriptions. It’s that easy!

Prescription prices may change over time, so be sure to use RxSaver to check the price of your medication every time you visit the pharmacy counter. "
"common_google_play_services_unsupported_text" : "%1$s won't run without Google Play services, which are not supported by your device."

"all_notification_description" : "Stay informed on the latest in pharmacy savings and app features."

"about_rxsaver_details" : "RxSaver is a free tool that can help you save up to 80%% on prescription medications at nearby pharmacies. Simply search for your prescription medication on our website or mobile app, and find coupons for pharmacies near you. RxSaver is easy to use and there are no membership fees.

Prescription drug prices vary across pharmacies. Your insurance program may not always provide you with the lowest price on your medication. Use the RxSaver app to find coupons to get discounted prices on prescriptions at pharmacies near you.

Search for your medication, then simply enter your ZIP code or use your GPS location to find pharmacies in your area. Once you’ve set the dosage and quantity details to match your prescription, select a pharmacy and get a coupon to show the pharmacist. They will enter the codes from the coupon to get you a lower price on your medication so you can get immediate savings.

Buying generic drugs can result in huge savings. The RxSaver app defaults to show generic drugs when available. You can tap “Edit Prescription Details” to select a brand name drug.

Some pharmacies offer discounted prices on certain drugs without the use of a coupon. These low cost medications are included in our price comparisons.

RxSaver coupons can save you money every time you purchase a prescription, and can be used at over 60,000 pharmacies nationwide. Even if you have insurance, you may be able to get a better price using RxSaver, so always check our prices before picking up your prescription.

For more information, go to
www.rxsaver.com

Copyright © RxSaver %1$d

App Version %2$s"

playstore_details.title: RxSaver – Prescription Coupons
playstore_details.description:
It’s your medication, only cheaper.  RxSaver™ lets you search for your prescription drug in seconds and finds you the cheapest prices at nearby pharmacies, so there are no surprises at the pharmacy counter.

RxSaver is free to use. No membership or sign in required. Whether you have insurance or not, you could be saving on your Rx medications.

Using RxSaver is as easy as 1-2-3.
1. 🔍Enter your medication in the app
2. 💊Get free Rx coupons to use at your pharmacy
3. 🎉Celebrate your savings. You’re now an RxSaver!

Where is RxSaver Accepted?
RxSaver coupons are accepted at all major U.S. pharmacies including: Walgreens, Walmart, CVS, Costco, Rite Aid, Kmart, Sam’s Club, Kroger, Duane Reade, HEB, Meijer, Publix, Randall’s, Safeway, and more. No matter where you fill your prescription, RxSaver can help you get good savings off the retail price of your Rx medication.

How Much Does RxSaver Cost?
RxSaver is free to use. There are no membership fees or sign in required. 

How Does the RxSaver App Work?
It’s simple and easy. Just install the app, search for your prescription medication, edit the dosage as needed, and get the coupon you want. Using the “Save Med” button you can keep your rx medication information handy for quick price checks anytime. 

Can I Use Rx Coupons With Insurance or Without Insurance?
RxSaver can be used by anyone who is insured, underinsured, or without insurance coverage. If the RxSaver coupon offers a better price than your health care insurance copay, simply use the coupon instead of your insurance for the prescription. Lower your out-of-pocket costs and feel good about your Rx savings.

RxSaver is NOT INSURANCE. RxSaver coupons cannot be combined with federal/state-funded health care programs like Medicaid or Medicare.

Can I use RxSaver at the pharmacy drive-thru? What about delivery?
RxSaver is your single savings solution for home delivery, drive-thru, and pick-up from your local pharmacy. Just call ahead to give the pharmacist the coupon information over the phone, or read the codes at the drive-thru. RxSaver also allows you to compare drug prices between local and online pharmacies with free home delivery. 

Do RxSaver Coupons Work on Refills?
Good news, RxSaver coupons never expire and you can keep the coupon on file at the pharmacy for all your refills. However, prescription prices can change over time. Searching for your medication through the RxSaver app is the best way to see current coupon prices.

How is the RxSaver App Different from Rx Discount Cards?
Paper Rx discount cards can get lost, but the RxSaver app is always free and easy to access on your device. The RxSaver app is a digital rx discount card that is always available when you need it and is the single easiest way to save at the pharmacy. The RxSaver app offers instant rx coupons on demand. 

Does RxSaver Work For Rx Pet Meds?
If your pet needs prescription drugs, you don’t have to pay full-price! RxSaver offers free coupons for pet meds that have human equivalents, which can be easily filled at local pharmacies. Ask your vet before filling your pet's next prescription.

Please visit https://www.goodrx.com/consumer-health-data-privacy-notice to read our Consumer Health Data Privacy Notice for additional information about our handling of consumer health data.

warning.title: Broadcast Receiver (com.google.firebase.iid.FirebaseInstanceIdReceiver) is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.
warning.description:
Permission: com.google.android.c2dm.permission.SEND [android:exported=true]
A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. It is protected by a permission which is not defined in the analysed application. As a result, the protection level of the permission should be checked where it is defined. If it is set to normal or dangerous, a malicious application can request and obtain the permission and interact with the component. If it is set to signature, only applications signed with the same certificate can obtain the permission.

hotspot.title: Found 3 critical permission(s)
hotspot.description:
Ensure that these permissions are required by the application.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION (dangerous): fine (GPS) location - Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION (dangerous): coarse (network-based) location - Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (dangerous): read/modify/delete external storage contents - Allows an application to write to external storage.
